# Repository Pattern

This project uses the Repository Pattern to decouple data access from controllers.

## Structure

- `app/Repositories/BaseRepository.php` — abstract base with `all()`, `find()`, `create()`, `update()`, `delete()`, `paginate()`, `allQuery()`, `allQueryLike()`
- `app/Repositories/{Model}Repository.php` — extends `BaseRepository`, implements `model()` and `getFieldsSearchable()`
- `app/Http/Controllers/AppBaseController.php` — base controller with `sendResponse()`, `sendError()`, `sendSuccess()`
- `app/Http/Controllers/API/{Model}APIController.php` — injects repository via constructor, uses `AppBaseController` responses

## Creating a New Repository

```php
// app/Repositories/PostRepository.php
namespace App\Repositories;

use App\Models\Post;

class PostRepository extends BaseRepository
{
    protected $fieldSearchable = ['title', 'status'];

    public function getFieldsSearchable(): array
    {
        return $this->fieldSearchable;
    }

    public function model(): string
    {
        return Post::class;
    }
}
```

## Creating a New API Controller

```php
// app/Http/Controllers/API/PostAPIController.php
namespace App\Http\Controllers\API;

use App\Http\Controllers\AppBaseController;
use App\Repositories\PostRepository;
use Illuminate\Http\JsonResponse;

class PostAPIController extends AppBaseController
{
    public function __construct(private PostRepository $postRepository) {}

    public function show(int $id): JsonResponse
    {
        $post = $this->postRepository->find($id);

        if (!$post) {
            return $this->sendError('Post not found.', 404);
        }

        return $this->sendResponse($post, 'Post retrieved successfully');
    }
}
```

## Rules

- **Never query Eloquent models directly in controllers.** All DB access goes through the repository.
- **Always inject the repository** via the constructor using constructor property promotion.
- **Use `sendResponse()`, `sendError()`, `sendSuccess()`** from `AppBaseController` — never return `response()->json()` directly in API controllers.
- **Put business logic in the repository**, not the controller. Controllers handle HTTP concerns only (auth, request parsing, response formatting).
- **Add custom query methods to the specific repository**, not to the controller or model.
- **Searchable fields** are declared in `$fieldSearchable` and returned by `getFieldsSearchable()`.
